<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="appointment-n">appointment <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /əˈpɔɪntmənt/    美 /əˈpɔɪntmənt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>约会；约定；预约：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>make / keep an appointment</strong>
预约/守约</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>I have an appointment with</strong> my dentist at 11:30.
我约好11点半去看牙医。</p><footer>2016 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Viewing is <strong>by appointment only</strong>.
参观必须预约。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>任命；任职；职位：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He holds an appointment in the English Department at present.
他目前在英语系任职。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They congratulated him on his <strong>appointment as</strong> chairman.
他们祝贺他被任命为主席。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>I have an appointment ______ Dr. Smith, but I need to change it.   （2013 北京改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. with  </p></div>